## üîß Setup Instructions

### 1. Development (.env.local)
```bash
# Copy this template
cp .env.example .env.local

# Fill in your development values
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-dev-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-dev-anon-key

# Sentry is optional in development
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=

# PostHog is optional in development
# VITE_POSTHOG_KEY=
```

### 2. Staging (Vercel Environment Variables)
```bash
# In Vercel Dashboard ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
# Set environment: "Preview"

STAGING_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-staging-project.supabase.co
STAGING_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-staging-anon-key
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn
VITE_POSTHOG_KEY=your-posthog-key
```

### 3. Production (Vercel Environment Variables)
```bash
# In Vercel Dashboard ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
# Set environment: "Production"

PRODUCTION_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-prod-project.supabase.co
PRODUCTION_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-prod-anon-key
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn
VITE_POSTHOG_KEY=your-posthog-key
```

### 4. GitHub Actions Secrets
```bash
# In GitHub Repository ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Secrets and Variables ‚Üí Actions
#Add the following secrets:

# Vercel
VERCEL_TOKEN=your-vercel-token
VERCEL_ORG_ID=your-org-id
VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id

# Supabase (for different environments)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=production-url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=production-key
STAGING_SUPABASE_URL=staging-url
STAGING_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=staging-key

# Monitoring
SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn
POSTHOG_KEY=your-posthog-key

# Testing
TEST_MANAGER_EMAIL=test@example.com
TEST_MANAGER_PASSWORD=secure-password
```

